               <msContents>
                  <summary>Two receipts for "adaeratio" of taxes in kind which were written on the same day: the first refers to payment made by Kopres; in the second the payers are the "sitologoi" of the village of Ptolemais; the receiver was Eulogios</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers with 19 lines; the back is blank</note>
                     <note type="general">Mark of kollesis in the middle of the first col.; broken at right and damaged</note>
                     <note type="general">Very fast ligatured hand that is difficult to read</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
